headline.main: TAFT GAINED PEAKS IN UNUSUAL CAREER; Mr. Taft at Different Stages of His Career. At Work on the Bench. A Hard-Working Chief Justice. Mr. Taft's Last Illness.

snippet: Twenty-seventh President of the United States and its tenth Chief Justice, William Howard Taft was the only man in the history of the couptry to become the head of both the Executive and Judicial Departments of the Federal Government.
